Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
    Author process-monitor-prep
    Description "Base image for the Process Monitor task – provides Python, pytest and a writable /home/user."

%post
    set -eux

    # Update package index and install needed tools
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        procps      \
        iputils-ping \
        coreutils    \
        ca-certificates

    # Install pytest for the autograder
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Create writable /home/user directory for the student
    mkdir -p /home/user
    # Make it world-writable so whichever UID runs inside the container can write
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    # Ensure no leftover artefacts from earlier builds
    rm -rf /home/user/process_monitor || true

    # Clean up
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Minimal, non-invasive environment setup
    export PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

%runscript
    echo "Process Monitor task container – ready for action."

%help
    This Apptainer image supplies:
      • Python 3
      • pytest (for the autograder)
      • Standard POSIX utilities (yes, ps, etc.)
    A writable /home/user is prepared. No task artefacts are present yet.